People tend to get the idea of what an 'infinite' is versus what a 'loop' is. Infinites -Keep going til an opponent dies, runs out of time, or even after that. -work if there's no infinite prevention system in place. Loops -Repeatable combo sequence that only lasts as long as the game allows.

For loops, what I mean is usually games have hit decay or juggle limits that could prevent you from doing certain things in a combo. I wouldn't call it an infinite prevention system because it usually would just be hard cutoff like what JJBAHFTF has. You can do whatever you want til it stops you.

So I finally got on with watching Gundam Requiem For Vengeance. Still got 2 episodes to go but it’sfine. I wish I could be more glowing but it’sfine. I like how it effectively portrays how terrifying the Gundam could be to fight, kinda like how they do it in the Cucuruz Doan manga.

I also think it’s cool in the second episode to watch the characters piloting a Zaku tank with the cockpit partially exposed because it’s been cut open on one side. It’s something I don’t recall seeing too much in Gundam. That was neat.

I don’t dislike the characters. Solari is a perfectly fine lead, though I hope we get to see more of her backstory before the end. Also, and I admit this is a small point, but I don’t like how the characters don’t look like they don’t belong in the year 0079.
It’s something that always kinda irks me when you have a new tale set during a particular part in the timeline of a franchise, but the characters look like they’re from a different era.

I actually felt this way about GQuuuuuuX too. Like, I know it’s not the same world exactly, but should the characters in 0085 be kinda dressed like characters in Zeta Gundam since that took place in the original timeline’s 0087?
And that’s not to say the character designs look bad in either of these, it’s just a small thing that bothers me when I see it happen in anything.

Anyway, Requiem For Vengeance. It’s okay. Definitely not the best short series Gundam has to offer. Like, it’s nowhere near as good as 0080 or even 0083. If anything it reminds me of MS-Igloo which I was also kinda lukewarm towards. Have to see how I feel by the end of the show, I guess.
